@node features
@{b}The Main Features.@{ub}

Works with any icon system.

Upto 32 individual or combined categories.

`Root description' search's as well as normal name search's.

Packed save files smaller than LHA.

Built in help: Just press the help key.

+muchmore that I can't be bothered to type in!
@endnode

@node Introduction
@{b}Introduction.@{ub}

Have you got lots of icons on your harddrive? If so, IdB is for you.

IdB allows you to effectively store and categorise these icons, making
finding that elusive icon as easy as possible.

IdB is a dedicated icon database.

@{i}{I've just had an idea (ouch)! You could use IdB as a picture catalog by
using a program such as `PictIcon' to create an icon of a picture, then
use IdB as normal but define the categories as different picture types!}
@{ui} 
IdB will work with any icon system (ie. @{" NewIcons " link NewICONS}, @{" MagicWb " link MAGICWB} and @{" IconoGfx " link ICONOGFX}).
It allows you to store any individual icon or full collection of icons,
and then retrieve or view those icon(s) in a useable manner.

Please note that this program is a beta version.  There is still some
work to be carried out.  Although this program has been thoroughly
tested I cannot be held responsible for any damage or loss of data
caused by the use of the program.

This version is SHARWARE and therefore limited to saving a database of
just 50 icons.  Registering costs just Ł5 (UK pounds).  

See @{"Registering" link registration}


STOP PRESS:
This program appears to be WB3+ only, and I've no idea why!  I am sure
I've not used any 3.0 specific commands but it will not work on a 2.04
based Amiga.  I can compile it ok with no errors on a wb2 machine but
when I run it I get a complete system crash - oh for a bug free Blitz!
@endnode

@node installation
@{b}How to Install IdB.@{ub}

Just click on the install-IdB icon or for a manual installation:

For IdB to work fully a few files need to be placed in the correct
directories:

If you wish to use the compression features of IdB:

Copy @{" XPK " link XPK} to C:xpk
Copy xpkmaster.library to LIBS:xpkmaster.library
Copy xpkNUKE.library to LIBS:Compressors/xpkNUKE.library

Now the main IdB installation:

Copy IdB.Categories to S:IdB.Categories

Copy IdB and the documentation to wherever you wish.

If you wish to use the lockcolors program:

Copy LockColors.cfg to S:lockcolors.cfg
Copy Lockcolors to WBStartup/lockcolors

For the colours to appear correct use a 64? colour wbscreen.

@endnode

