@node todo
@{b}To Do.@{ub}

I plan on developing IdB for as long as there is interest in this
program. IdB as been under constant development already for over 6
months, and as such is a different program now compared with the
original development idea. I have some distinct ideas of how I want Idb
to develop these include:

Linking into a picture catalogue - possibly using a program like
PictIcon or ImageFx via AREXX.

A less memory intensive display system using paging rather than
overlapping windows.

Independent screen use. The ability to use its own screen may be usefull
but would require using different palettes for different icon
collections.

As I say, I have some ideas, but I would like to hear yours too.  If you
want to send me an idea or just a note to say how useful you find IdB
then please do.

After doing somemore fixes to this program I am getting really pissed
off with Blitz - not the language itself - but one library: The Reqtools
one - see bugs, so I'm considering re-writing this in C or E, so wish me
luck as, at yet I can't do either!

